title: Teku fails to start: IllegalArgumentException: State must belong to the given block
body:

Version: `teku/v0.12.7-dev-10c2471c/linux-x86_64/-privatebuild-openjdk64bitservervm-java-13` (this is almost up to date, but also running the validator performance patch from Cem. After an epoch of seeing only empty slots, Teku went into sync mode after this, but remained stuck at slot 395423, and frequently producing the above error, always for block 395424. Now I am unable to restart.
Closing for now as likely due to a hardware fault (memory errors) and not a bug in Teku.
